parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Burning smell from the left side of the steering wheel
high beams work but low beams do not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the IMA (Integrated Motor Assist) battery can cause sudden loss of power, hesitation, and lack of acceleration, leading to increased risk of accidents, especially when merging onto highways or accelerating on ramps.
symptoms: rapid discharge of the IMA battery
"recall events" (sudden and unexpected loss of IMA assist).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic control module can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including power windows, power steering, and digital dashboard readings, leading to increased risk of accidents and reduced vehicle safety.
symptoms: power windows and power steering fail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the state of charge gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the IMA battery's true state of charge, leading to sudden loss of power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: State of charge gauge no longer accurately reports the state of charge of the IMA battery
sudden and unexpected loss of IMA boost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS/airbag system can lead to unexpected airbag deployment, causing accidents, injuries, and fatalities. Moreover, a faulty system can also fail to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: SRS light comes on and stays on
failure of airbags to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle. It can also lead to loss of control, swerving, and collision.
Failure of the seat belt retractor can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: failure of seat belt to restrain occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden failure of the low beam headlights can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The low beam headlights suddenly fail to illuminate
requiring the driver to switch to high beams to continue driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Honda's refusal to cover the cost of repairs for vehicles with similar issues, despite a recall being issued, can lead to frustration and mistrust among customers, potentially affecting their loyalty to the brand.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are denied repair coverage due to their VIN not being included in the recall
despite experiencing the same issue as described in the recall
leading to disappointment and frustration with the manufacturer's customer service.
